{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17641657","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17641657"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:29:50+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:29:50+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17893"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17893","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17893"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10607"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78477"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10607","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10607"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17893"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63839"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"11228"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24719"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24722"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78477","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78477"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following molecules is used to activate acetoacetate to acetoacetyl-CoA in tissues that oxidise ketone bodies?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Butyryl-CoA","Succinyl-CoA","Hydroxymethylglutaryl-CoA","Propionyl-CoA","Malonyl-CoA"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn the metabolism of ketone bodies, \u003Cstrong\u003Esuccinyl-CoA\u003C/strong\u003E is used to convert acetoacetate to acetoacetyl-CoA in peripheral tissues. This reaction is catalysed by the enzyme succinyl-CoA:acetoacetate CoA transferase, also known as thiophorase. This step is crucial for the utilisation of ketone bodies as an energy source, especially during periods of fasting or low carbohydrate intake.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EButyryl-CoA\u003C/strong\u003E is not involved in the activation of acetoacetate. It is a short-chain fatty acyl-CoA involved in fatty acid metabolism.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMalonyl-CoA\u003C/strong\u003E is a key intermediate in fatty acid synthesis, not in ketone body metabolism.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHydroxymethylglutaryl-CoA\u003C/strong\u003E is involved in the synthesis of ketone bodies in the liver, not in their utilisation in peripheral tissues.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPropionyl-CoA\u003C/strong\u003E is an intermediate in the metabolism of certain amino acids and odd-chain fatty acids, not in ketone body metabolism.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Ketone bodies are metabolised in peripheral tissues by converting acetoacetate to acetoacetyl-CoA using succinyl-CoA.","The conversion of acetoacetate to acetoacetyl-CoA is a crucial step in the utilisation of ketone bodies for energy.","Understanding the metabolic pathways of ketone bodies is important in conditions like diabetes and prolonged fasting."],"references":["Bender, D. A., \u0026 Cunningham, S. M. (2021). Introduction to nutrition and metabolism. CRC Press","Salway, J. G. (2016). Metabolism at a Glance. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Judge A, Dodd MS. Metabolism. Essays Biochem. 2020 Oct 8;64(4):607-647. doi: 10.1042/EBC20190041. PMID: 32830223; PMCID: PMC7545035","Wang Y, Wu R. The Effect of Fasting on Human Metabolism and Psychological Health. Dis Markers. 2022 Jan 5;2022:5653739. doi: 10.1155/2022/5653739. PMID: 35035610; PMCID: PMC8754590","Nakrani MN, Wineland RH, Anjum F. Physiology, Glucose Metabolism. 2023 